## data_base
\f1 \

\f0 The purpose is to generate a database in another language. For now, it is generating a french database. All the files  are to be executed with Pyhton 3, as well as SQL Lite (a library used to implement SQL databases).
\f1 \
\

\f0 \'93schema.png\'94 is the database schema in French.
\f1 \
\

\f0 #generation_pyhton
\f1 \

\f0 The file \'ab\'a0main.py\'a0\'bb is to be executed to generate the entire database. It generates the database in the same directory as \'93main.py\'94. It executes the file \'93create.py\'94 and \'93fill.py\'94 as well as putting the clues in the database. The file \'93create.py\'94 is used to generate the different tables of the database, and the file \'93fill.py\'94 is used to fill the database. 
\f1 \
\

\f0 #model_txt
\f1 \

\f0 All files in this directory are used to fill in the databse. 
\f1 \

\f0 \'93cities_list.txt\'94 is a list of the 277 biggest French towns, based on a Wikipedia list.
\f1 \

\f0 \'93makers_list.txt\'94 is a list of the 60 car brands most used in France.
\f1 \

\f0 \'93noise_text.txt\'94 is the text of a novel : \'93Le myst\'e8re de la chambre jaune\'94 by Gaston Leroux. It is provided by the Project Gutenberg and is free to use. We use this text to fill the crime descriptions in the table crime_scene_report.
\f1 \

